 TARGET SELECTION 


      LSPM-N 
      ALL-sky Bright M Dwarfs


       Magnitude & Color Cuts

           7 < H < 12 
           V - K > 5.0 
      0.4 < J - H < 0.65
      0.1 < H - K < 0.42



OUR SAMPLE 

      1404 M Dwarfs 

       253 M Dwarfs observed
       at the end of Year One

       1127 H-band spectra  

 SCIENCE WITH 
M DWARFS IN NEAR-INFRARED


 VSINI 

  
vsini of 210 M dwarfs measured

   Precision ~ 2 - 3 km/s

  ~400 M dwarfs have 
 known vsini in literature

  This survey will more than
  double this number 

RELATIVE RADIAL VELOCITIES



  

Use of telluric lines + 
  forward modeling to 
  derive relative RVs

  Relative RV precision:
    ~50 - 150 m/s 

  Identified 43 potential 
  binaries  


M Dwarf Binaries in APOGEE Sample 

                2D cross-correlation Implementaion  

AO Imaging 

 

AO Imaging at Keck & Palomar provides detection
of wide binaries 

Metallicity 

Deriving high resolution empirical relation for M Dwarfs

                                                   Use of K I , Ca I    
                                                           and water features     
        
                                              Spectral Type 
                                               determination 


Moving Forward 

Coma Ber low-mass Secondary  


CONCLUSIONS 

  • On-going survey of 1404 M dwarfs with APOGEE

  • Deriving vsini, absolute RV, and metallicity 

  • Deriving relative RV & AO imaging to detect close 
    and wide companions, respectively

  • This will be the largest hi-res. spectroscopic H-band
    M dwarf survey to date
